unittitle_ssm: Theodore Francis Jones Papers
abstract_ssm: Theodore Francis Jones was born in Dover, Massachusetts on December 5, 1885. He joined the Department of History at New York University as an instructor in 1910 and was assistant professor, 1920-1924, and professor, 1924-1951. He also served as Director of Gould Memorial Library on the University Heights campus from 1925 to 1948. His book, New York University, 1832-1932, was published in 1933 as part of the university's centennial celebration. Upon his retirement in 1951, Jones was awarded an honorary degree by NYU. He died on November 18, 1968. The collection contains research notes, official and military correspondence, reports, and the manuscript of New York University, 1832-1932.
